{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":881,"text":"I have a question."},{"time":3422,"text":"Can a computer write poetry?"},{"time":6959,"text":"This is a provocative question."},{"time":9715,"text":"You think about it for a minute,"},{"time":11457,"text":"and you suddenly have a bunch\nof other questions like:"},{"time":14769,"text":"What is a computer?"},{"time":16710,"text":"What is poetry?"},{"time":18707,"text":"What is creativity?"},{"time":21650,"text":"But these are questions"},{"time":22846,"text":"that people spend their entire\nlifetime trying to answer,"},{"time":25940,"text":"not in a single TED Talk."},{"time":28188,"text":"So we're going to have to try\na different approach."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30657,"text":"So up here, we have two poems."},{"time":33839,"text":"One of them is written by a human,"},{"time":36139,"text":"and the other one's written by a computer."},{"time":38754,"text":"I'm going to ask you to tell me\nwhich one's which."},{"time":41858,"text":"Have a go:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":43038,"text":"Poem 1: Little Fly / Thy summer's play, /\nMy thoughtless hand / Has brush'd away."},{"time":47118,"text":"Am I not / A fly like thee? /\nOr art not thou / A man like me?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":50536,"text":"Poem 2: We can feel / Activist\nthrough your life's / morning /"},{"time":53859,"text":"Pauses to see, pope I hate the / Non\nall the night to start a / great otherwise (...)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":58130,"text":"Alright, time's up."},{"time":59513,"text":"Hands up if you think Poem 1\nwas written by a human."},{"time":65547,"text":"OK, most of you."},{"time":67061,"text":"Hands up if you think Poem 2\nwas written by a human."},{"time":71172,"text":"Very brave of you,"},{"time":72855,"text":"because the first one was written\nby the human poet William Blake."},{"time":77784,"text":"The second one was written by an algorithm"},{"time":80757,"text":"that took all the language\nfrom my Facebook feed on one day"},{"time":84473,"text":"and then regenerated it algorithmically,"},{"time":87260,"text":"according to methods that I'll describe\na little bit later on."},{"time":91218,"text":"So let's try another test."},{"time":94398,"text":"Again, you haven't got ages to read this,"},{"time":96515,"text":"so just trust your gut."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98151,"text":"Poem 1: A lion roars and a dog barks.\nIt is interesting / and fascinating"},{"time":102220,"text":"that a bird will fly and not / roar\nor bark. Enthralling stories about animals"},{"time":106547,"text":"are in my dreams and I will sing them all\nif I / am not exhausted or weary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110631,"text":"Poem 2: Oh! kangaroos, sequins, chocolate\nsodas! / You are really beautiful!"},{"time":114640,"text":"Pearls, / harmonicas, jujubes, aspirins!\nAll / the stuff they've always talked about (...)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":119022,"text":"Alright, time's up."},{"time":120204,"text":"So if you think the first poem\nwas written by a human,"},{"time":123365,"text":"put your hand up."},{"time":125687,"text":"OK."},{"time":126865,"text":"And if you think the second poem\nwas written by a human,"},{"time":129564,"text":"put your hand up."},{"time":131779,"text":"We have, more or less, a 50/50 split here."},{"time":136157,"text":"It was much harder."}]},{"cues":[{"time":137617,"text":"The answer is,"},{"time":139353,"text":"the first poem was generated\nby an algorithm called Racter,"},{"time":142860,"text":"that was created back in the 1970s,"},{"time":145886,"text":"and the second poem was written\nby a guy called Frank O'Hara,"},{"time":149099,"text":"who happens to be\none of my favorite human poets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152631,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":156046,"text":"So what we've just done now\nis a Turing test for poetry."},{"time":160018,"text":"The Turing test was first proposed\nby this guy, Alan Turing, in 1950,"},{"time":164589,"text":"in order to answer the question,"},{"time":166177,"text":"can computers think?"},{"time":168245,"text":"Alan Turing believed that if\na computer was able"},{"time":171039,"text":"to have a to have a text-based\nconversation with a human,"},{"time":174141,"text":"with such proficiency\nsuch that the human couldn't tell"},{"time":176935,"text":"whether they are talking\nto a computer or a human,"},{"time":179925,"text":"then the computer can be said\nto have intelligence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":183270,"text":"So in 2013, my friend\nBenjamin Laird and I,"},{"time":186589,"text":"we created a Turing test\nfor poetry online."},{"time":189601,"text":"It's called bot or not,"},{"time":190902,"text":"and you can go and play it for yourselves."},{"time":192970,"text":"But basically, it's the game\nwe just played."},{"time":195245,"text":"You're presented with a poem,"},{"time":196797,"text":"you don't know whether it was written\nby a human or a computer"},{"time":199849,"text":"and you have to guess."},{"time":201039,"text":"So thousands and thousands\nof people have taken this test online,"},{"time":204254,"text":"so we have results."}]},{"cues":[{"time":205727,"text":"And what are the results?"},{"time":207704,"text":"Well, Turing said that if a computer\ncould fool a human"},{"time":210607,"text":"30 percent of the time\nthat it was a human,"},{"time":213650,"text":"then it passes the Turing test\nfor intelligence."},{"time":216625,"text":"We have poems on the bot or not database"},{"time":219087,"text":"that have fooled 65 percent\nof human readers into thinking"},{"time":222090,"text":"it was written by a human."},{"time":223959,"text":"So, I think we have an answer\nto our question."},{"time":227546,"text":"According to the logic of the Turing test,"},{"time":229918,"text":"can a computer write poetry?"},{"time":231870,"text":"Well, yes, absolutely it can."},{"time":235782,"text":"But if you're feeling\na little bit uncomfortable"},{"time":238152,"text":"with this answer, that's OK."},{"time":240103,"text":"If you're having a bunch\nof gut reactions to it,"},{"time":242443,"text":"that's also OK because\nthis isn't the end of the story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":246594,"text":"Let's play our third and final test."},{"time":250000,"text":"Again, you're going to have to read"},{"time":251774,"text":"and tell me which you think is human."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253707,"text":"Poem 1: Red flags the reason\nfor pretty flags. / And ribbons."},{"time":257449,"text":"Ribbons of flags / And wearing material /\nReasons for wearing material. (...)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":261794,"text":"Poem 2: A wounded deer leaps\nhighest, / I've heard the daffodil"},{"time":265736,"text":"I've heard the flag to-day /\nI've heard the hunter tell; /"},{"time":269206,"text":"'Tis but the ecstasy of death, /\nAnd then the brake is almost done (...)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":272932,"text":"OK, time is up."},{"time":274555,"text":"So hands up if you think Poem 1\nwas written by a human."},{"time":279973,"text":"Hands up if you think Poem 2\nwas written by a human."},{"time":283035,"text":"Whoa, that's a lot more people."},{"time":286327,"text":"So you'd be surprised to find that Poem 1"},{"time":289319,"text":"was written by the very\nhuman poet Gertrude Stein."},{"time":294100,"text":"And Poem 2 was generated\nby an algorithm called RKCP."},{"time":299162,"text":"Now before we go on, let me describe\nvery quickly and simply,"},{"time":302505,"text":"how RKCP works."},{"time":304873,"text":"So RKCP is an algorithm\ndesigned by Ray Kurzweil,"},{"time":308747,"text":"who's a director of engineering at Google"},{"time":310993,"text":"and a firm believer\nin artificial intelligence."},{"time":313822,"text":"So, you give RKCP a source text,"},{"time":317837,"text":"it analyzes the source text in order\nto find out how it uses language,"},{"time":322330,"text":"and then it regenerates language"},{"time":324302,"text":"that emulates that first text."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326854,"text":"So in the poem we just saw before,"},{"time":328991,"text":"Poem 2, the one that you all\nthought was human,"},{"time":331640,"text":"it was fed a bunch of poems"},{"time":333214,"text":"by a poet called Emily Dickinson"},{"time":335273,"text":"it looked at the way she used language,"},{"time":337486,"text":"learned the model,"},{"time":338675,"text":"and then it regenerated a model\naccording to that same structure."},{"time":344732,"text":"But the important thing to know about RKCP"},{"time":346934,"text":"is that it doesn't know the meaning\nof the words it's using."},{"time":350359,"text":"The language is just raw material,"},{"time":352659,"text":"it could be Chinese,\nit could be in Swedish,"},{"time":354843,"text":"it could be the collected language\nfrom your Facebook feed for one day."},{"time":359046,"text":"It's just raw material."},{"time":361380,"text":"And nevertheless, it's able\nto create a poem"},{"time":364101,"text":"that seems more human\nthan Gertrude Stein's poem,"},{"time":367452,"text":"and Gertrude Stein is a human."}]},{"cues":[{"time":370846,"text":"So what we've done here is,\nmore or less, a reverse Turing test."},{"time":375940,"text":"So Gertrude Stein, who's a human,\nis able to write a poem"},{"time":381143,"text":"that fools a majority\nof human judges into thinking"},{"time":384905,"text":"that it was written by a computer."},{"time":387176,"text":"Therefore, according to the logic\nof the reverse Turing test,"},{"time":391341,"text":"Gertrude Stein is a computer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":393281,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":395358,"text":"Feeling confused?"},{"time":397193,"text":"I think that's fair enough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":399546,"text":"So far we've had humans\nthat write like humans,"},{"time":403686,"text":"we have computers that write\nlike computers,"},{"time":406821,"text":"we have computers that write like humans,"},{"time":409900,"text":"but we also have,\nperhaps most confusingly,"},{"time":413556,"text":"humans that write like computers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416938,"text":"So what do we take from all of this?"},{"time":419611,"text":"Do we take that William Blake\nis somehow more of a human"},{"time":422792,"text":"than Gertrude Stein?"},{"time":424065,"text":"Or that Gertrude Stein is more\nof a computer than William Blake?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":427135,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":428711,"text":"These are questions\nI've been asking myself"},{"time":431058,"text":"for around two years now,"},{"time":432547,"text":"and I don't have any answers."},{"time":434880,"text":"But what I do have are a bunch of insights"},{"time":437234,"text":"about our relationship with technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":440999,"text":"So my first insight is that,\nfor some reason,"},{"time":444632,"text":"we associate poetry with being human."},{"time":448197,"text":"So that when we ask,\n\"Can a computer write poetry?\""},{"time":451936,"text":"we're also asking,"},{"time":453153,"text":"\"What does it mean to be human"},{"time":454975,"text":"and how do we put boundaries\naround this category?"},{"time":458171,"text":"How do we say who or what\ncan be part of this category?\""},{"time":462376,"text":"This is an essentially\nphilosophical question, I believe,"},{"time":465751,"text":"and it can't be answered\nwith a yes or no test,"},{"time":468004,"text":"like the Turing test."},{"time":469805,"text":"I also believe that Alan Turing\nunderstood this,"},{"time":472874,"text":"and that when he devised\nhis test back in 1950,"},{"time":476203,"text":"he was doing it\nas a philosophical provocation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":481124,"text":"So my second insight is that,\nwhen we take the Turing test for poetry,"},{"time":486689,"text":"we're not really testing\nthe capacity of the computers"},{"time":490173,"text":"because poetry-generating algorithms,"},{"time":493090,"text":"they're pretty simple and have existed,\nmore or less, since the 1950s."},{"time":499055,"text":"What we are doing with the Turing\ntest for poetry, rather,"},{"time":502197,"text":"is collecting opinions about what\nconstitutes humanness."},{"time":508313,"text":"So, what I've figured out,"},{"time":511066,"text":"we've seen this when earlier today,"},{"time":514062,"text":"we say that William Blake\nis more of a human"},{"time":516564,"text":"than Gertrude Stein."},{"time":518153,"text":"Of course, this doesn't mean\nthat William Blake"},{"time":520639,"text":"was actually more human"},{"time":522491,"text":"or that Gertrude Stein\nwas more of a computer."},{"time":525533,"text":"It simply means that the category\nof the human is unstable."},{"time":531450,"text":"This has led me to understand"},{"time":533548,"text":"that the human is not a cold, hard fact."},{"time":536832,"text":"Rather, it is something\nthat's constructed with our opinions"},{"time":539988,"text":"and something that changes over time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544671,"text":"So my final insight is that\nthe computer, more or less,"},{"time":549174,"text":"works like a mirror\nthat reflects any idea of a human"},{"time":553204,"text":"that we show it."},{"time":554958,"text":"We show it Emily Dickinson,"},{"time":556866,"text":"it gives Emily Dickinson back to us."},{"time":559768,"text":"We show it William Blake,"},{"time":561626,"text":"that's what it reflects back to us."},{"time":563935,"text":"We show it Gertrude Stein,"},{"time":565798,"text":"what we get back is Gertrude Stein."},{"time":569083,"text":"More than any other bit of technology,"},{"time":571475,"text":"the computer is a mirror that reflects\nany idea of the human we teach it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":578061,"text":"So I'm sure a lot of you have been hearing"},{"time":580372,"text":"a lot about artificial\nintelligence recently."},{"time":584694,"text":"And much of the conversation is,"},{"time":588292,"text":"can we build it?"},{"time":590383,"text":"Can we build an intelligent computer?"},{"time":593542,"text":"Can we build a creative computer?"},{"time":596329,"text":"What we seem to be asking over and over"},{"time":598466,"text":"is can we build a human-like computer?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":601961,"text":"But what we've seen just now"},{"time":603541,"text":"is that the human\nis not a scientific fact,"},{"time":606653,"text":"that it's an ever-shifting,\nconcatenating idea"},{"time":610207,"text":"and one that changes over time."},{"time":612762,"text":"So that when we begin\nto grapple with the ideas"},{"time":615938,"text":"of artificial intelligence in the future,"},{"time":618348,"text":"we shouldn't only be asking ourselves,"},{"time":620277,"text":"\"Can we build it?\""},{"time":621669,"text":"But we should also be asking ourselves,"},{"time":623587,"text":"\"What idea of the human\ndo we want to have reflected back to us?\""},{"time":627820,"text":"This is an essentially philosophical idea,"},{"time":630537,"text":"and it's one that can't be answered\nwith software alone,"},{"time":633558,"text":"but I think requires a moment\nof species-wide, existential reflection."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639040,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":640217,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}